Create a complete interactive high-fidelity mobile application prototype for a Human-Computer Interaction project titled “Smart Mall Navigation & Shopping Assistant.” The prototype must be fully connected screen-to-screen with realistic navigation flow, clickable interactions, transitions, overlays, and live prototype behavior suitable for Figma presentation mode and real application preview.

The prototype should directly follow the storyboard scenario:
A shopper enters a crowded mall searching for black cargo pants, becomes confused by unclear signs, opens the Smart Mall app, searches for the product, receives recommended stores and low-crowd navigation routes, then successfully reaches the destination store.

The interface must visually match the existing low-fidelity prototype, storyboard, affinity diagram, personas, and presentation theme.

Visual Style Requirements:

* Apple-inspired minimalist mobile UI
* Futuristic smart shopping assistant aesthetic
* Light gray grid background
* Dark blue, bright blue, white, and soft gray color palette
* Glassmorphism cards with frosted transparency
* Rounded corners and smooth geometry
* Soft shadows and subtle depth
* Thin modern outlines
* Elegant typography hierarchy
* Modern sans-serif fonts
* Consistent spacing and alignment
* Clean visual hierarchy
* Premium interface quality similar to Apple Maps and modern shopping applications
* Consistent design system across all screens

UX Goals:

* Reduce navigation confusion
* Improve product discovery
* Avoid crowded areas
* Reduce unnecessary walking
* Provide real-time shopping guidance
* Improve shopping efficiency and comfort

